    <h1 id="bookh1">Prenatal Care - 3rd Month</h1>
    

    
    <h3>Nutrition</h3>
    <p>
        During the 3rd month of pregnancy, your baby's development is rapidly progressing. Maintain a healthy diet by focusing on the following:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Increase your intake of nutrient-rich foods like leafy greens, whole grains, and fruits.</li>
        <li>Continue to include a variety of protein sources such as poultry, fish, and plant-based options.</li>
        <li>Consume foods rich in folate, like lentils and spinach, to support neural tube development.</li>
        <li>Stay well-hydrated and drink plenty of water throughout the day.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Exercises</h3>
    <p>
        Regular exercise remains essential during the 3rd month of pregnancy. Here are some safe exercises to consider:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Prenatal strength training can help maintain muscle tone and strength.</li>
        <li>Pilates can improve posture and flexibility while being gentle on the body.</li>
        <li>Deep breathing and relaxation exercises can reduce stress and promote overall well-being.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Always consult with your healthcare provider before starting any new exercise routine or making significant dietary changes.
    </p>

